&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Fellow Anaesthesia &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;East Surrey &amp; Crawley Hospitals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full time - 40 hours per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fixed term - 12 months&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary - £32,478 - £51,069 per annum plus 1A Banding Supplement (50%).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surrey &amp; Sussex NHS Healthcare Trust wishes to appoint a full-time Clinical Fellow. This is a fixed term 12 month appointments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will join a team of 36 Consultants, 10 SAS Grades, up to 24 Trainees, 3 Acute Pain Nurses and 4 administrative staff. The department is friendly, engaged and provides excellent training. You would be expected to work flexibly through the week with commitment to the on-call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are general and the successful appointees will work as an integral part of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will provide 40 hours per week of flexible working in theatres, as a part of the trainee on call rota which rolls over an 8 week period. The successful candidates will be given SPA time and encouraged to take part in departmental teaching, clinical governance and QI activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East Surrey is the principle hospital for emergencies and inpatients, with day case surgery at Crawley Hospital. Anaesthetists are expected to be available across both hospital sites dependant on operational requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are welcomed by contacting Dr Afolake Bewaji (afolake.bewaji@nhs.net) or Dr Christie Locke (christie.locke@nhs.net) or on 01737 768511 ext. 6046 / 6938.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: TBC (via Skype - East Surrey Hospital)&lt;/p&gt;
